<h2>7. Text2Infographic — Best AI Infographic Generator for Content Repurposing</h2>
<p>Text2Infographic is built for one job: turning existing content into infographics. Paste a blog post URL, upload a document, or enter text directly. The AI extracts key points, generates a visual structure, and produces a shareable infographic.</p>
<h3>What It Does Well</h3>
<p>The blog-to-infographic converter is the headline feature. Enter any URL and Text2Infographic scans the page, identifies headings, statistics, and key takeaways, and builds an infographic around them. The AI adds automatic citations linking back to the original source.</p>
<p>Brand color customization is straightforward. Enter your brand hex codes and the AI applies them to every element. The tool supports 20+ languages, making it useful for global content teams.</p>
<p>The lifetime pricing model is unique. Pay $70 once and get unlimited access. This is a fraction of the cost of monthly subscriptions for tools like Canva Pro or Visme Business.</p>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>Our Take:</strong> Text2Infographic is the tool we use when we want to squeeze extra value from a high-performing blog post. The URL-to-infographic feature works well on structured articles with clear headings. It struggles with narrative or opinion pieces without data points.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3>Where It Falls Short</h3>
<p>Template variety is limited compared to Canva or Venngage. The credit system on lower tiers can be restrictive for high-volume users. The AI sometimes misses nuanced points from complex articles.</p>
<h3>Key Features</h3>
<ul>
<li>Blog post and URL-to-infographic conversion</li>
<li>Automatic source citations on generated visuals</li>
<li>Brand color customization with hex code input</li>
<li>20+ language support</li>
<li>Text, URL, and file input options</li>
